  "prompt": "What are G4 nations?",
  "response": "The G4 nations refer to a group of four countries: Brazil, Germany, India, and Japan. These countries have expressed a shared interest in reforming the United Nations Security Council (UNSC) to make it more representative of the current global geopolitical landscape. The G4 nations advocate for permanent membership on the Security Council, believing that they can contribute significantly to global peace and security given their economic and political influence.\n\nThe group is also often associated with efforts to promote cooperation among its members in various global and regional issues, as well as a commitment to multilateralism. The G4's proposals for UNSC reform have been part of broader discussions on enhancing the effectiveness and legitimacy of the UN in addressing contemporary challenges.",
